cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the problem of crafting adversarial examples for neural networks, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer security (cs.CR), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SI). The paper proposes a new gray-box approach to crafting adversarial examples against defenses that obfuscate gradients, which is relevant to all of these sub-fields. Therefore, it is likely that this paper could be classified under any of these sub-categories, with cs.LG and cs.CR being the most likely due to the focus on machine learning and security.
